Sentencas: In this work, three highly active anode materials are developed to effectively catalyze hydrogen and hydrocarbons in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Robust in situ exsolved nanocatalysts on perovskite oxide as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A-site deficient (Pr0.5Ba0.5)(0.9)MnO3-delta materials doped with different Fe contents (PBM1-yFy, y = 0, 0.2, 0.4) have a typical cubic-hexagonal heterostructure.
Titulo: Robust in situ exsolved nanocatalysts on perovskite oxide as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is indicated that (Pr,Ba)O-x nanoparticles are homogeneously in situ exsolved from the parent PBM1-yFy oxides during the reduction process to form PBO@LPBMF anode materials, exhibiting good electro-catalytic activity and considerable stability towards both hydrogen and propane fuels, which can be explained by the improved electro-catalytic properties and good carbon coking resistance of the in situ exsolved (Pr,Ba)O-x nanoparticles.
Titulo: Robust in situ exsolved nanocatalysts on perovskite oxide as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is also found that the La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta electrolyte-supported single cell with the PBO@LPBM0.8F0.2 anode exhibits better electrochemical performance than the PBO@LPBM0.6F0.4 anode.
Titulo: Robust in situ exsolved nanocatalysts on perovskite oxide as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum peak power density of the single cell with the optimal PBO@LPBM0.8F0.2 anode is 489 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C when fueled with propane.
Titulo: Robust in situ exsolved nanocatalysts on perovskite oxide as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our findings obtained can guide the development of other ceramic electrodes for energy conversion and storage devices.
Titulo: Robust in situ exsolved nanocatalysts on perovskite oxide as an efficient anode for hydrocarbon fueled solid oxide fuel cells
